63 // Compute centering offet to be applied to our meshes so that we work with smaller coordinates
64 // requiring less bits to represent Clipper coordinates.
65
66 // Snug bounding box of a rotated and scaled object by the 1st instantion, without the instance translation applied.
67 // All the instances share the transformation matrix with the exception of translation in XY and rotation by Z,
68 // therefore a bounding box from 1st instance of a ModelObject is good enough for calculating the object center,
69 // snug height and an approximate bounding box in XY.
70 BoundingBoxf3 bbox = model_object->raw_bounding_box();
71 Vec3d bbox_center = bbox.center();
72 // We may need to rotate the bbox / bbox_center from the original instance to the current instance.
73 double z_diff = Geometry::rotation_diff_z(model_object->instances.front()->get_rotation(), instances.front().model_instance->get_rotation());
74 if (std::abs(z_diff) > EPSILON) {
75 auto z_rot = Eigen::AngleAxisd(z_diff, Vec3d::UnitZ());
76 bbox = bbox.transformed(Transform3d(z_rot));
77 bbox_center = (z_rot * bbox_center).eval();
78 }
79
80 // Center of the transformed mesh (without translation).
81 m_center_offset = Point::new_scale(bbox_center.x(), bbox_center.y());
82 // Size of the transformed mesh. This bounding may not be snug in XY plane, but it is snug in Z.
83 m_size = (bbox.size() * (1. / SCALING_FACTOR)).cast<coord_t>();
